article.headline: Colorado St. 79, Mayville State 42
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Dorian Green's game-high 17 points helped lead Colorado State to a 79-42 victory over Mayville State on Tuesday night. Green was 5 for 8 from the field and 3 for 3 from 3-point range. He also managed four steals. Andy Ogide added 13 points and eight rebounds for the Rams (3-2). Greg Smith contributed 10 points off the bench. Marcus Carson led the Comets with 16 points. He was 7 for 12 from the field. Alfonzo McNeal added 10, the only other Comet in double digits. Ross Aman grabbed four offensive rebounds and eight total. The Rams defense held the Comets to just 13 first-half points and took a 35-13 lead into the half.
